WEBVTT

00:10.378 --> 00:13.114
Guys, come on, talk to me!

00:14.882 --> 00:16.484
<i>Habla, por favor?</i>

00:16.617 --> 00:18.052
<i>Yo soy abogado!</i>

00:18.186 --> 00:19.453
<i>Abogado! Abogado!</i>

00:19.587 --> 00:21.889
Oh. Crap,
you already knew that.

00:22.022 --> 00:23.657
Jesus, fellas?

00:23.791 --> 00:24.992
There's a better way
to do this!

00:25.759 --> 00:27.328
Hello?

00:27.461 --> 00:30.164
Ohh. Why are we--
why are we going off-road?

00:30.298 --> 00:32.533
Ohh! Ohh!

00:32.666 --> 00:35.569
Whatever this is,
can we please,
don't do it in the desert?

00:35.703 --> 00:37.071
Anywhere but the desert!

00:37.205 --> 00:40.208
Oh! Oh, God, I'm gonna be sick.

00:43.844 --> 00:46.247
Ahh. Ahh.

00:47.381 --> 00:50.751
This, we can-- we can fix this.

00:50.884 --> 00:54.122
Whatever the problemo,
we can fix it with <i>dinero.</i>

00:54.255 --> 00:56.023
<i>Mucho dinero.</i>

00:56.157 --> 00:58.058
<i>Mucho, mucho, mucho dinero.</i>

00:58.192 --> 01:00.094
Come on, please.

01:00.228 --> 01:01.662
One of you, just you talk.

01:01.795 --> 01:02.863
<i>Habla.</i>

01:02.996 --> 01:05.433
Come on,
before mistakes are made.

01:05.566 --> 01:07.501
Come on, talk to me, guys, huh?

01:07.635 --> 01:09.903
Please, come on,
just tell me what you want!

01:10.037 --> 01:10.971
Geez!

01:12.573 --> 01:13.374
Whoa!

01:14.775 --> 01:16.644
Oh, no, no, no, no, no!

01:16.777 --> 01:18.346
No! It wasn't me!

01:18.479 --> 01:20.348
It was Ignacio! He's the one!

01:56.884 --> 01:59.287
You can't put seeds and stems
in the sink.

02:00.488 --> 02:02.122
Put what or what?

02:02.256 --> 02:03.491
Seeds and stems.

02:03.624 --> 02:05.493
You can't put them
down the drain.

02:05.626 --> 02:08.061
Uh, we didn't do that.

02:08.196 --> 02:09.197
Then what's this?

02:10.398 --> 02:12.633
Regular sink stuff.

02:12.766 --> 02:14.935
Listen,
if you're gonna do this shit,

02:15.068 --> 02:16.704
at least flush it
down the toilet, not the sink.

02:16.837 --> 02:18.672
W-What're you, my mom?

02:18.806 --> 02:20.308
We don't have drugs here.

02:21.141 --> 02:22.276
Uh-huh.

02:22.410 --> 02:24.178
You don't believe us.

02:24.312 --> 02:25.946
She doesn't believe us.

02:26.079 --> 02:29.417
You sleep past noon,
you don't seem to have
regular employment.

02:29.550 --> 02:32.586
Plus, your whole place
smells like a skunk's butthole.

02:32.720 --> 02:35.689
Also, your sink is full
of stems and seeds.

02:35.823 --> 02:37.725
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Look, narca,

02:37.858 --> 02:39.360
we're not doing drugs,

02:39.493 --> 02:41.995
so stop trying to cast,
y'know...

02:44.665 --> 02:46.166
aspersions.

02:46.300 --> 02:47.568
Narca?

02:47.701 --> 02:48.769
Yeah. "Narca."

02:48.902 --> 02:50.638
The feminine version
of "narco."

02:51.972 --> 02:53.507
Conjugate much?

03:02.350 --> 03:04.184
I gotta go.

03:04.318 --> 03:06.387
Just leave the plunger outside
the door when you're done.

03:06.520 --> 03:09.223
But, uh,
it's still clogged, dude.

03:09.357 --> 03:11.792
You do it, dude.

03:11.925 --> 03:13.227
Hold up, where you goin'?

03:13.361 --> 03:15.529
Yo, lady, we pay rent.

03:15.663 --> 03:16.630
You can do it.

03:16.764 --> 03:18.399
It's a simple
up and down motion,

03:18.532 --> 03:19.667
like you're used to.

04:49.222 --> 04:50.758
Okay. Okay.

04:50.891 --> 04:51.759
Okay.

06:11.472 --> 06:12.540
Yeah.

06:12.673 --> 06:15.308
<i>Oh, good.
You're there. Great.</i>

06:16.043 --> 06:17.377
<i>Great.</i>

06:17.511 --> 06:19.780
<i>Unencumbered by curious
eyes and ears, I'm guessing.</i>

06:19.913 --> 06:21.214
Wouldn't have
picked up otherwise.

06:21.348 --> 06:21.882
<i>Right.</i>

06:22.783 --> 06:23.717
Excellent.

06:23.851 --> 06:26.053
Um, okay. Well, then.

06:26.186 --> 06:27.788
Lay it on me.

06:27.921 --> 06:28.856
<i>First things first.</i>

06:30.057 --> 06:32.726
No. I... I believe
we agreed "after."

06:33.894 --> 06:34.728
I'm hanging up.

06:34.862 --> 06:35.763
Okay! Okay, then!

06:35.896 --> 06:36.864
Geez, I...

06:40.167 --> 06:42.970
Okay, if you're...
if you're facing the phone,

06:43.103 --> 06:46.239
turn right 90 degrees
and, uh, walk straight.

06:46.373 --> 06:49.877
<i>You'll see some pieces
of broken concrete in the dirt.</i>

06:50.010 --> 06:54.214
Just pull back the one that's
kinda shaped like New Jersey.

06:54.347 --> 06:55.549
<i>New Jersey?</i>

06:55.683 --> 06:57.585
Alfred Hitchcock in a fez.

06:57.718 --> 06:58.852
Whatever.

06:58.986 --> 07:00.888
<i>Just</i>
<i>pull that one back,</i>

07:01.021 --> 07:03.491
<i>and you'll see
a, um, soda can tab.</i>

07:03.624 --> 07:05.058
<i>It's got a fishing line
tied to it.</i>

07:05.192 --> 07:06.460
Follow that line,

07:06.594 --> 07:08.228
it'll take you
to an old water line,

07:08.361 --> 07:09.963
and just keep pulling
the string,

07:10.097 --> 07:11.965
<i>and you'll get what I promised.</i>

08:11.391 --> 08:12.492
<i>Okay.</i>

08:12.626 --> 08:13.894
Great. Was it all there?

08:14.027 --> 08:15.896
I mean, the rats
didn't eat it or anything?

08:16.029 --> 08:17.197
<i>It's all here.</i>

08:19.466 --> 08:23.971
Okay, well, uh,
tell me, how hot?

08:24.805 --> 08:25.939
How hot?

08:26.073 --> 08:26.874
<i>Yeah.</i>

08:27.007 --> 08:29.743
Well... I still get followed.

08:29.877 --> 08:32.379
Not as often as when
the shit first hit the fan,

08:32.512 --> 08:34.347
but I still see them.

08:35.783 --> 08:38.185
My mail gets opened.

08:38.318 --> 08:42.122
My phone at home clicks
whenever I use it.

08:42.255 --> 08:45.192
So the maestro buying the farm,
it didn't change anything?

08:45.325 --> 08:47.728
<i>No. If anything,
it made it worse.</i>

08:47.861 --> 08:49.396
Skyler White got her deal.

08:49.529 --> 08:51.531
So the only ones left
to go after

08:51.665 --> 08:52.900
are you and Pinkman.

08:53.033 --> 08:54.568
And I heard they found his car
down by the border,

08:54.702 --> 08:57.404
so, <i>adios,</i> dopehead.

08:57.537 --> 08:59.239
Oh, so they're still into me.

09:02.209 --> 09:03.977
Well...

09:04.111 --> 09:05.813
Hey, what do you know
about the nail salons?

09:05.946 --> 09:07.414
<i>Nail salons are gone.</i>

09:07.547 --> 09:09.717
Wha-- Gone? All of them?

09:09.850 --> 09:10.684
<i>Yep.</i>

09:12.185 --> 09:13.520
What about
the vending machines?

09:13.654 --> 09:15.022
<i>- Gone.</i>
- Jesus!

09:16.023 --> 09:18.525
Ah, don't tell me... Laser tag?

09:18.659 --> 09:20.093
Feds found it all, Saul.

09:20.227 --> 09:21.528
<i>But how?</i>

09:21.662 --> 09:24.031
<i>It was shells within shells!</i>

09:24.164 --> 09:25.132
<i>Damn it!</i>

09:25.265 --> 09:27.034
Damn it, okay...

09:28.468 --> 09:29.269
Okay.

09:30.537 --> 09:32.940
Hey, oh, what if--

09:33.073 --> 09:35.542
Let's say there was
an overseas account,

09:35.676 --> 09:37.577
um, Antigua and Barbuda--

09:37.711 --> 09:39.546
Tigerfish Corporation?

09:39.680 --> 09:41.649
<i>- What?</i>
- Tigerfish Corporation?

09:41.782 --> 09:44.051
$850k? I gave it to the feds.

09:44.184 --> 09:46.319
You did what?
Why would you do that?

09:46.453 --> 09:47.420
<i>Time has expired.</i>

09:47.554 --> 09:49.089
God damn it!

09:49.222 --> 09:50.423
<i>- Please deposit...</i>
- <i>You--</i> <i>You put my name</i>

09:50.557 --> 09:52.259
<i>on the board
of a fictional corporation.</i>

09:52.392 --> 09:54.161
I had to give it up.
I didn't really have a choice.

09:54.294 --> 09:56.930
A-And a heads up
would've been nice, by the way.

09:58.065 --> 10:00.400
<i>So it's gone?</i>

10:00.533 --> 10:01.969
<i>It's all gone?</i>

10:02.102 --> 10:03.937
Those sons of bitches
took everything.

10:04.071 --> 10:05.605
<i>Except what you took with you.</i>

10:05.739 --> 10:07.875
<i>And I'm guessing
that wasn't chump change.</i>

10:09.777 --> 10:11.144
Yeah. Well...

10:13.146 --> 10:14.081
Well.

10:15.916 --> 10:17.484
Guess that's it. <i>- Wait, wait, wait.</i>

10:17.617 --> 10:19.186
Come on,
I just put more quarters in.

10:19.319 --> 10:22.155
Can't you just, I don't know,

10:22.289 --> 10:23.791
gimme the lowdown.

10:23.924 --> 10:24.992
<i>There's nothing else.</i>

10:25.125 --> 10:26.293
Well, that's not true.

10:26.426 --> 10:28.461
After all this time? Come on.

10:28.595 --> 10:30.097
Just fill me in.

10:31.198 --> 10:34.101
What-- Um, how's Kuby?

10:34.935 --> 10:36.636
No idea.

10:36.770 --> 10:37.905
<i>All right, how about Huell?</i>

10:39.139 --> 10:40.708
Huell.

10:40.841 --> 10:43.677
I guess back home
in New Orleans.

10:43.811 --> 10:45.813
DEA held him under
false pretenses or something,

10:45.946 --> 10:47.781
so last I heard, he walked.

10:49.016 --> 10:52.019
Good. Um, how about Danny?

10:52.152 --> 10:54.254
Or, uh, or Ira?

10:54.387 --> 10:55.622
I mean,
any word on those two guys?

10:57.024 --> 10:59.026
<i>They have Internet
where you are?</i>

10:59.159 --> 11:02.329
Well, just, come on,
give me something.

11:02.462 --> 11:03.964
There's gotta be some news.

11:06.599 --> 11:09.269
Uh, remember Bill Oakley?

11:09.402 --> 11:10.537
He switched sides.

11:11.404 --> 11:13.040
He came out, huh?

11:13.173 --> 11:14.674
<i>No, he's not gay.</i>

11:14.808 --> 11:16.043
He's a defense attorney now.

11:17.177 --> 11:18.045
<i>Huh.</i>

11:19.012 --> 11:22.015
Well, I mean, what about you?

11:22.149 --> 11:23.450
How are you doin'?

11:23.583 --> 11:24.885
<i>Oh, I'm just great.</i>

11:25.018 --> 11:27.120
Prince Rainier proposed.

11:27.254 --> 11:30.590
The private jet is taking us
to the palace on Thursday.

11:31.825 --> 11:33.526
<i>Yeah. Okay.</i>

11:33.660 --> 11:36.329
<i>Well, I guess that's it, then.</i>

11:42.635 --> 11:45.038
I did get one call.

11:45.172 --> 11:46.339
After everything went down.

11:49.376 --> 11:50.177
<i>Kim.</i>

11:51.812 --> 11:52.880
<i>Checking in on me.</i>

11:54.681 --> 11:56.016
No kidding?

11:56.884 --> 11:57.818
<i>Mm-hmm.</i>

12:00.020 --> 12:01.188
<i>Your name came up.</i>

12:02.522 --> 12:04.024
<i>Asked if you were alive.</i>

12:05.025 --> 12:06.193
She asked about me?

12:10.063 --> 12:11.498
What did you tell her?

12:11.631 --> 12:12.665
Nothing.

12:13.901 --> 12:15.102
<i>But she asked?</i>

12:15.235 --> 12:16.069
Yep.

12:25.712 --> 12:27.080
Oh, okay. Well...

12:28.148 --> 12:29.216
Uh, I guess...

12:30.750 --> 12:32.119
this is goodbye.

12:32.252 --> 12:34.221
Hello? Hello?

13:34.181 --> 13:36.283
Hi, I need a number in Florida.

13:36.416 --> 13:37.484
Titusville.

13:38.251 --> 13:40.120
Palm Coast Sprinklers.

13:41.521 --> 13:43.656
It's on a road, um...

13:45.158 --> 13:46.994
It's named after a fish.

13:47.127 --> 13:48.061
Uh...

13:48.962 --> 13:51.064
Tarpon Road, right.

13:51.198 --> 13:54.034
Uh, well, can you
put me through? I'll--

13:54.167 --> 13:55.535
Say again, how much?

13:55.668 --> 13:56.569
Okay.

14:11.384 --> 14:12.685
Hi.

14:12.819 --> 14:16.823
I'm looking for Kim Wexler.

14:16.957 --> 14:18.325
I believe she works there.

16:01.128 --> 16:03.130
Another good one.

16:03.263 --> 16:05.432
Oh, hey, Jeffie!
Look what the cat dragged in!

16:07.267 --> 16:08.635
Hey. Hey, Gene.

16:08.768 --> 16:09.936
Yeah. Your mom
was just showing me

16:10.070 --> 16:11.338
this computer you bought her.

16:11.471 --> 16:12.872
Yeah, well, he...
he got it for me,

16:13.006 --> 16:15.608
and I didn't know
what the hell
to do with it, but, uh,

16:15.742 --> 16:17.144
look, Gene showed me.

16:17.277 --> 16:19.946
- You... You go to the box up here...
- Mm-hmm.

16:20.080 --> 16:22.449
...and then you type in
"funny cat videos."

16:22.582 --> 16:25.385
I mean, that's it,
just "funny cat videos."

16:25.518 --> 16:29.022
These funny
cat videos just pop up!

16:29.156 --> 16:30.357
Look at this one. Look, look.

16:30.490 --> 16:32.459
Cat
eating an ice cream.

16:32.592 --> 16:34.027
Can you believe it?

16:34.161 --> 16:35.995
It's like <i>America's
Funniest Home Videos,</i>

16:36.129 --> 16:37.430
but you get to be the host.

16:37.564 --> 16:39.699
Ooh, wouldn't that
be something?

16:39.832 --> 16:41.568
Wow.

16:41.701 --> 16:44.737
Hey, uh, Jeffie,
get some glasses, and we can
pour the ol' Schnapps, huh?

16:44.871 --> 16:45.838
Yeah.

16:49.076 --> 16:51.678
I thought a computer would be
good for her, you know?

16:53.613 --> 16:54.681
It was on sale.

16:57.317 --> 16:59.919
Not a... big buy at all.

17:01.354 --> 17:03.856
Well, I think it's great.

17:03.990 --> 17:06.326
Treat your mom right,
that's what I say.

17:06.459 --> 17:07.694
- Hey, Marion...
- Hmm?

17:07.827 --> 17:10.497
How about, uh,
we leave you to the cat videos,

17:10.630 --> 17:14.033
and Jeff and I
take our drink to go?

17:14.167 --> 17:16.503
I mean, is that car running?
I'd love to take a gander.

17:17.904 --> 17:18.805
Come on.

17:21.841 --> 17:22.509
Okay.

17:33.886 --> 17:35.922
I swear, the computer's
the one big thing I bought,

17:36.055 --> 17:37.590
and it's not even that much.

17:37.724 --> 17:40.059
It's a... it's an old model
on discount.

17:40.193 --> 17:41.294
And nobody
said nothing to nobody.

17:41.428 --> 17:42.595
N-not me, not Buddy.

17:44.997 --> 17:46.733
Living our lives like normal,
just like you said.

17:46.866 --> 17:48.235
- Stop talking.
- But I want to--

17:48.368 --> 17:50.370
Jeff. Stop talking.

17:50.503 --> 17:51.871
I need you to answer
some questions.

17:52.004 --> 17:54.941
First up, you have
a night shift, right?

17:55.074 --> 17:56.409
You mean the graveyard shift?

17:56.543 --> 17:59.045
At the cab company? Yeah.

17:59.179 --> 18:00.113
What are the hours?

18:02.048 --> 18:04.751
They got a 9:00-to-6:00,
a midnight-to-9:00.

18:04.884 --> 18:07.720
- Why?
- Get on the 9:00-to-6:00.

18:07.854 --> 18:10.557
After that, we need to get
our hands on some barbiturates.

18:11.991 --> 18:12.592
What?

18:14.261 --> 18:15.395
You're shitting me?

18:17.230 --> 18:18.565
What're we gonna do with them?

18:22.569 --> 18:23.903
But you said we're done.

18:24.036 --> 18:27.207
You said, "Cross to
the other side of the street"

18:27.340 --> 18:28.575
if I see you coming.

18:37.550 --> 18:38.785
So we're back in business?

18:42.622 --> 18:43.923
Oh, hell, yeah.

18:46.559 --> 18:50.663
<i>♪ The sailor said
"Brandy, you're a fine girl" ♪</i>

18:50.797 --> 18:54.234
<i>♪ What a good wife
You would be ♪</i>

18:54.367 --> 18:59.506
<i>♪ But my life, my love
And my lady is the sea ♪</i>

18:59.639 --> 19:02.809
<i>♪ Do da-dit-dooda... ♪</i>

19:02.942 --> 19:06.145
<i>♪ At night
When the bars close down ♪</i>

19:06.279 --> 19:09.349
<i>♪ Brandy walks
Through a silent town ♪</i>

19:10.983 --> 19:13.620
<i>♪ And loves a man
Who's not around ♪</i>

19:13.753 --> 19:16.889
<i>♪ She can still hear him say ♪</i>

19:17.023 --> 19:17.890
<i>♪ She hears
Him say, "Brandy..." ♪</i>

19:18.024 --> 19:19.326
Brandy!

19:19.459 --> 19:20.993
<i>♪ "You're a fine girl" ♪</i>

19:21.127 --> 19:22.995
<i>♪ What a good wife
You would be ♪</i>

19:23.129 --> 19:25.131
<i>Con gusto!</i>

19:25.265 --> 19:30.036
<i>♪ But my life, my love
My lady is the sea ♪</i>

19:30.169 --> 19:33.240
<i>♪ Do da-dit-dooda... ♪</i>

19:33.373 --> 19:34.841
<i>♪ Doo doo-da doo-doo ♪</i>

19:39.111 --> 19:40.179
Wow.

19:40.313 --> 19:41.681
Ah.

19:42.349 --> 19:43.650
Wow.

19:44.351 --> 19:45.818
He did that.

19:45.952 --> 19:47.254
[karaoke singer sings
"Summer Breeze"
in the background]

19:47.387 --> 19:49.356
Ah-di-di-di-da-da.

19:49.489 --> 19:51.391
Well.

19:51.524 --> 19:53.560
That must've been
what it would be like

19:53.693 --> 19:55.695
if you watched
the <i>Hindenburg</i> go down.

19:55.828 --> 19:57.664
But worse,
am I right?

19:57.797 --> 20:00.300
- Yeah, well, with gusto, right?
- Gusto.

20:00.433 --> 20:04.604
- A bet's a bet.
- With gusto!

20:04.737 --> 20:06.739
Hey, what do you say
we go again?

20:06.873 --> 20:08.007
Up the stakes?

20:08.140 --> 20:09.809
Loser has to sing
with his shirt off this time--

20:09.942 --> 20:11.678
No, no, no. No more bets, okay?

20:11.811 --> 20:13.980
Come on,
I haven't been right once.

20:14.113 --> 20:16.383
Aw, what's the matter,
wittle fella,

20:16.516 --> 20:18.251
you haven't been wight once?

20:18.385 --> 20:19.686
Not once?

20:19.819 --> 20:21.454
Hey, can we get more peanuts?

20:21.588 --> 20:25.191
Come on, Viktor!

20:25.325 --> 20:26.559
Don't be a wuss.

20:26.693 --> 20:28.094
I'm not a wuss.

20:28.227 --> 20:29.696
That's right. You're not.

20:29.829 --> 20:33.600
You... You gotta believe
in yourself, little buddy.

20:36.068 --> 20:37.804
Let's do one more bet.
One more bet. One more bet.

20:37.937 --> 20:39.739
- No. No more.
- Come on, come on. Come on, come on.

20:39.872 --> 20:41.040
No more lemon wedges
on my nose,

20:41.173 --> 20:43.410
no more trick coins,
no more toothpick puzzles.

20:43.543 --> 20:45.578
I, I'm not good at this.

20:45.712 --> 20:46.546
Viktor.

20:47.514 --> 20:48.715
This is an easy one.

20:51.684 --> 20:55.087
Now, you grab the hundo
before I do,

20:55.221 --> 20:56.889
you get to keep it.

20:57.023 --> 21:00.226
I grab the hundo first,
you buy another round.

21:01.594 --> 21:04.831
Only rule is,
you can't move until I move.

21:04.964 --> 21:08.234
Yeah, but I'm...
I'm so much closer to it.

21:08.368 --> 21:09.736
It's like giving me the money.

21:10.937 --> 21:12.305
So you want to take the bet?

21:13.840 --> 21:15.742
Yeah, I'll take it.

21:22.048 --> 21:23.282
Oh, son of a bitch!

21:23.416 --> 21:24.751
Oh-oh-oh-oh-oh!

21:24.884 --> 21:27.754
You lose, sucker.

21:27.887 --> 21:31.458
Another round, good man,

21:31.591 --> 21:34.894
once again
courtesy of my little friend.

21:35.027 --> 21:37.530
All right, all right.

21:37.664 --> 21:40.333
Aw. You're fun.

21:44.236 --> 21:45.338
<i>Gracias.</i>

21:53.746 --> 21:56.315
Ah-di-di-di-da-da-
da-da-da-da-da-da-da.

22:01.921 --> 22:03.490
You know,
you're all right, Viktor.

22:03.623 --> 22:05.792
Yeah, I just wish
I knew how you did it.

22:05.925 --> 22:10.797
Well, you see,
I'm a man of many talents.

22:10.930 --> 22:14.701
And you
are a man of very few.

22:14.834 --> 22:16.202
Kidding!

22:16.335 --> 22:18.204
Kidding. Maybe.

22:21.240 --> 22:22.509
Ah.

22:22.642 --> 22:25.378
Every time, every time,
she'll never see it coming.

22:25.512 --> 22:27.179
Yeah.

22:27.313 --> 22:28.915
Shh-- Yeah...

22:29.048 --> 22:30.517
I need some night air.

22:30.650 --> 22:31.818
Well.

22:33.285 --> 22:34.721
Easy.

22:34.854 --> 22:36.956
Looks like
one of our cabs is here.

22:37.089 --> 22:39.892
Ohh. I'll bet you for it.

22:40.026 --> 22:42.161
No bets.

22:42.294 --> 22:43.596
Come on, now, hear me out.

22:43.730 --> 22:44.564
It's simple.

22:44.697 --> 22:46.232
Don't be such a pussy, baby.

22:47.700 --> 22:49.536
Look...

22:49.669 --> 22:50.803
What?

22:50.937 --> 22:53.072
Simple as simple can be.

22:53.205 --> 22:55.742
Balance this book of matches
on the back of your hand
for ten seconds.

22:56.809 --> 22:58.344
That's it, and the cab's yours.

22:59.345 --> 23:00.447
I'll even pay for it.

23:00.580 --> 23:02.148
You're just gonna punch me
or something...

23:02.281 --> 23:05.485
No, I promise.
My hands won't touch your body.

23:05.618 --> 23:07.587
And I won't blow it off
the back of your hand.

23:07.720 --> 23:08.655
Really?

23:10.089 --> 23:14.360
My body
will not touch your body

23:14.494 --> 23:15.261
or the matches.

23:16.262 --> 23:17.229
[scoffs, chuckling] Fine.

23:17.363 --> 23:18.565
- Huh?
- I gotta win one, right?

23:18.698 --> 23:20.433
All right.

23:20.567 --> 23:21.868
That's right, you do.

23:22.001 --> 23:22.902
Okay, now.

23:24.370 --> 23:25.037
Count with me.

23:26.105 --> 23:27.774
Ten...

23:27.907 --> 23:30.477
- Nine, eight...
- Nine, eight...

23:30.610 --> 23:33.079
Jesus! Jesus!

23:33.212 --> 23:34.881
Loser!

23:37.750 --> 23:40.152
I'll see you around
next time, pal.

23:40.286 --> 23:40.953
This was fun!

23:42.722 --> 23:44.323
Oh, and, Viktor,

23:45.725 --> 23:46.893
you can keep the matches.

23:48.595 --> 23:51.063
<i>♪ What a fine girl ♪</i>

23:51.197 --> 23:54.233
<i>♪ Do da-dit-dooda... ♪</i>

24:12.785 --> 24:13.920
You call for a ride?

24:14.621 --> 24:15.822
Nah. I'm good.

24:55.494 --> 24:57.096
<i>♪ Do da-dit-dooda... ♪</i>

24:58.464 --> 24:59.331
<i>♪ Do da-dit-dooda... ♪</i>

25:04.671 --> 25:05.638
You okay back there?

25:06.773 --> 25:08.174
Yeah. I'm fine.

25:08.307 --> 25:12.211
Got a lotta booze
and, uh, nuts in my mouth.

25:13.980 --> 25:16.549
I got water here, if you want.

25:16.683 --> 25:17.383
On the house.

25:28.360 --> 25:29.261
<i>Car 357,
what's your status?</i>

25:31.798 --> 25:34.533
Yeah, car 357,

25:34.667 --> 25:36.535
I'm about ten minutes away
from my drop

25:36.669 --> 25:39.038
at, uh, 17 Del Mar Place.

25:41.040 --> 25:43.309
357, head to the airport
when you're done.

25:43.442 --> 25:45.511
<i>Copy that.</i>

26:14.741 --> 26:15.875
You doing okay, sir?

26:20.780 --> 26:21.714
Yeah. I'm fine.

26:31.257 --> 26:32.424
Hey, you can go.

26:33.392 --> 26:35.427
I'm not giving you another tip.

26:36.562 --> 26:37.630
No problem, sir.

26:45.772 --> 26:46.773
Feel better.

32:08.027 --> 32:10.729
What the hell is this?

32:10.862 --> 32:14.133
It's like James Whale's
travelling road show in here.

32:14.266 --> 32:15.667
Whoever the hell that is.

32:15.801 --> 32:17.069
The Crystal Ship
definitely travels.

32:19.238 --> 32:22.374
I'm sorry,
you said the "what" travels?

32:22.508 --> 32:24.943
Crystal Ship.
It's what I call this thing.

32:25.077 --> 32:28.114
All right. Never mind.
Just-- No details.

32:28.247 --> 32:30.116
We're paying him to do a job,
let's just leave it at that.

32:30.249 --> 32:32.118
No details? Fellas, that--

32:32.251 --> 32:33.319
that money
you put in my pocket,

32:33.452 --> 32:35.254
that doesn't
just extend to this job.

32:35.387 --> 32:37.189
That will get you
attorney-client privilege

32:37.323 --> 32:38.790
on, on all matters.

32:38.924 --> 32:40.092
No. Details.

32:40.226 --> 32:41.760
Look at this set-up.

32:41.893 --> 32:44.663
I-- What, you two drive
around like Mister Softee,

32:44.796 --> 32:46.932
scooping out drugs
for all the good boys
and girls?

32:47.066 --> 32:47.833
No, we don't deal from here.

32:48.667 --> 32:50.836
I said, "No details."

32:50.969 --> 32:52.671
Dude is standing
in front of a meth lab.

32:52.804 --> 32:54.140
It's not like he ain't gonna
put two and two together.

32:54.273 --> 32:56.342
He is on a need-to-know basis.

32:56.475 --> 32:58.244
Oh. I didn't wanna
show my face.

32:58.377 --> 33:00.279
Did he need to know that?

33:00.412 --> 33:02.214
So, you're not
just distribution.

33:02.348 --> 33:04.783
You're the whole
freakin' package.

33:07.319 --> 33:10.289
You two
actually make the blue stuff.

33:12.458 --> 33:13.259
Here?

33:14.560 --> 33:16.462
That's amazing.

33:17.363 --> 33:18.997
Can you not touch--

33:19.131 --> 33:20.566
I mean, look at this.

33:20.699 --> 33:23.069
I had a fish that could've used
this as a vacation home.

33:23.202 --> 33:26.004
But you're using it
to make the goods, huh?

33:26.138 --> 33:28.340
Yeah. That's a, uh,
round-bottom flask.

33:28.474 --> 33:31.043
- Mm.
- Right?

33:31.777 --> 33:32.478
Round-bottom?

33:35.381 --> 33:37.849
It's a flask for distilling.

33:37.983 --> 33:39.651
It won't be if you break it.

33:39.785 --> 33:41.487
Now, please, put it down.

33:42.821 --> 33:47.226
Okay, so,
if you cook the blue stuff,

33:47.359 --> 33:48.494
then that means
you're Igor and--

33:48.627 --> 33:49.995
And that makes you--

33:51.830 --> 33:52.898
You're Heisenberg.

33:53.865 --> 33:54.700
Wow.

33:56.235 --> 33:57.903
Hey, tell me, how--

33:58.036 --> 34:00.339
How much product
can you churn out
with a set-up like this?

34:00.472 --> 34:02.341
No, we're done.
We're done with the questions.

34:02.474 --> 34:04.910
Mm. <i>- We</i> ask the questions.

34:05.043 --> 34:07.879
You have a job, one job,

34:08.013 --> 34:09.348
and I still don't understand

34:09.481 --> 34:10.549
how you're
going to pull it off.

34:10.682 --> 34:12.084
Listen, when I get
all my ducks in a row,

34:12.218 --> 34:14.253
I'll give you a PowerPoint
down at the office.

34:14.386 --> 34:16.688
But until then, just...
just bring what
we talked about, okay?

34:16.822 --> 34:19.091
And don't worry,
I'm gonna make it work.

34:19.225 --> 34:20.426
I'm taking the $80,000

34:20.559 --> 34:23.061
as a starting point
for negotiation.

34:23.195 --> 34:25.531
Take it any way you want,
that's the price.

34:25.664 --> 34:27.699
And, uh...
I'm callin' shotgun.

34:33.172 --> 34:33.939
I will drive.

34:35.374 --> 34:39.945
Oh, yeah, sure,
I'll just stand, I guess.

34:40.078 --> 34:41.513
Dick.

34:41.647 --> 34:43.115
At least you won't be
rolling around

34:43.249 --> 34:44.516
like the last Christmas ham

34:44.650 --> 34:45.851
in the back
of the delivery truck.

34:45.984 --> 34:47.119
You know, I--

34:47.253 --> 34:48.754
I've got bad knees.

34:48.887 --> 34:51.123
Think you might've
messed up my rotator cuff.

34:51.257 --> 34:53.425
You're lucky I'm not charging
you for my chiropractor.

34:53.559 --> 34:54.826
She's expensive.

34:54.960 --> 34:57.062
But she adjusts everything.

35:01.467 --> 35:03.101
Damn it.

35:03.235 --> 35:04.570
You gotta give it some gas
when you're backing up.

35:04.703 --> 35:07.406
I gave it
the proper amount of gas.

35:07.539 --> 35:08.740
I guess that's why
we're moving, then.

35:08.874 --> 35:10.976
Look, it just was idling
too long.

35:11.109 --> 35:12.744
It'll start.

35:14.045 --> 35:15.547
Oh, you shoulda
just let me drive, yo.

35:15.681 --> 35:17.716
Look, nothing
would be different
in this moment

35:17.849 --> 35:19.951
except you panicking
and flooding the engine.

35:20.085 --> 35:21.587
Bullshit.

35:21.720 --> 35:23.955
Fellas, I was enjoying
the Laurel and Hardy vibe,

35:24.089 --> 35:25.991
but I'm not such a fan
of the Bickersons.

35:26.124 --> 35:28.294
Now, can you get me
back to my office?

35:28.427 --> 35:30.962
I, I got work to do if you
want me to make some magic.

35:31.096 --> 35:33.299
We just need to sit a moment.

35:33.432 --> 35:34.700
That's all.

35:34.833 --> 35:38.003
When it idles too long,
the fuel pump overheats,

35:38.136 --> 35:40.105
and so we just need
to let it cool down.

36:14.072 --> 36:15.006
So.

36:15.974 --> 36:17.008
Who's Lalo?

36:18.777 --> 36:20.111
Who?

36:20.246 --> 36:21.880
Lalo.

36:22.013 --> 36:23.649
You thought some dude
named Lalo sent us.

36:23.782 --> 36:25.551
You seemed pretty freaked out.

36:26.952 --> 36:28.654
Never heard of no Lalo
on the street.

36:32.057 --> 36:33.425
It's nobody.

36:33.559 --> 36:37.563
Hey, are you gonna
try that again, 'cause--

36:37.696 --> 36:39.865
or are they gonna find us,
you know, buried in a sandstorm

36:39.998 --> 36:41.066
a thousand years from now?

36:41.199 --> 36:41.900
Just please.

36:55.881 --> 36:57.182
Bravo.

36:57.316 --> 36:58.950
I second that.

36:59.084 --> 37:02.087
And let me give you
two free words of advice.

37:02.220 --> 37:04.623
Jiffy Lube.

37:04.756 --> 37:05.891
Hold on.

38:42.754 --> 38:44.089
Where did you read that?

38:44.222 --> 38:46.291
<i>Personal Finance for Dummies?</i>

38:46.425 --> 38:47.693
I mean, is it wrong?

38:47.826 --> 38:49.661
Yeah. Big time.

38:51.563 --> 38:53.599
Don't put all your eggs
in one basket, genius.

38:53.732 --> 38:57.302
<i>♪ Reasoned verse
Some prose or rhyme ♪</i>

38:57.436 --> 38:58.837
Yeah, this is mine.

38:58.970 --> 39:01.206
<i>♪ Lose themselves
In other times ♪</i>

39:01.339 --> 39:05.210
<i>♪ And waiting hopes
Cast silent spells ♪</i>

39:05.343 --> 39:07.513
<i>♪ That speak in clouded clues ♪</i>

39:07.646 --> 39:10.716
- How about a water?
- Sure. Thanks.

39:10.849 --> 39:12.984
<i>♪ It cannot be a part of me ♪</i>

39:13.118 --> 39:16.021
<i>♪ For now it's part of you ♪</i>

39:19.157 --> 39:22.160
<i>♪ Careful plays on fields ♪</i>

39:22.293 --> 39:26.865
<i>♪ That seem to vanish
When they're in between ♪</i>

39:26.998 --> 39:31.002
