<i>♪ For now it's part of you ♪</i>

41:57.482 --> 41:58.183
You wanna know my trick?

41:59.450 --> 42:01.319
Play your own game,

42:01.452 --> 42:03.521
don't get caught up with
what the other guys are buying.

42:03.655 --> 42:04.489
Mm-hmm.

42:04.623 --> 42:06.057
Like the man says,

42:06.191 --> 42:09.194
you never know
who's swimming nude
until the tide goes out.

42:09.327 --> 42:11.997
I guess.

42:12.130 --> 42:14.532
But, I mean,
with this financial stuff,

42:14.666 --> 42:16.267
it feels like
the game is rigged.

42:16.401 --> 42:17.669
The big guys
always win.

42:17.803 --> 42:19.104
Well...

42:19.237 --> 42:21.907
I wish I could disagree
with you, Viktor, but I can't.

42:22.040 --> 42:23.975
There is definitely dishonesty.

42:24.109 --> 42:28.346
But the majority, I believe,
are straight shooters.

42:28.479 --> 42:31.016
Now, the...
the folks responsible

42:31.149 --> 42:32.718
for, uh,

42:32.851 --> 42:34.920
Enron, WorldCom...

42:35.053 --> 42:37.022
Madoff and his ilk...

42:37.155 --> 42:38.924
Mm.

42:39.057 --> 42:40.626
...I gotta believe
there's a special place in Hell

42:40.759 --> 42:41.693
for those people.

42:41.827 --> 42:42.594
Yeah.

42:44.696 --> 42:48.433
But in my experience,
that's the exception.

42:48.566 --> 42:53.371
Y-You can't let
a few bad apples
spoil it for the rest of us.

42:53.504 --> 42:55.373
In fact--

42:55.506 --> 42:56.742
Sorry.

43:10.521 --> 43:11.723
Those look exotic.

43:12.758 --> 43:14.425
I-I went through that phase.

43:14.559 --> 43:16.427
I took every vitamin there was.

43:16.561 --> 43:19.064
Hey, guess
how many pills I took

43:19.197 --> 43:20.331
to try to keep the hair
on my head.

43:20.465 --> 43:21.967
Worked like a charm.

43:23.301 --> 43:24.302
What are those for?

43:27.005 --> 43:28.573
Cancer.

43:30.942 --> 43:32.577
Oh.

43:32.711 --> 43:33.544
Sorry.

43:35.380 --> 43:36.247
Uh.

43:37.916 --> 43:41.086
Uh, is it, uh... is it bad?

43:41.987 --> 43:43.088
Well, it ain't the good kind.

43:45.423 --> 43:47.926
Come on. More drinks.
This one's on me.

43:48.059 --> 43:49.094
Get two more here, please?

43:55.166 --> 43:56.434
Hey, uh,
it's none of my business,

43:56.567 --> 43:57.468
but, um...

43:58.603 --> 44:00.105
should you be drinkin'?

44:06.812 --> 44:08.346
You only go around once.

44:12.417 --> 44:13.284
You got that right.

44:36.674 --> 44:38.476
You sure you don't want to
take this one, Vik?

44:38.609 --> 44:39.644
I can wait.

44:39.778 --> 44:40.946
No. It's all you.

44:41.079 --> 44:42.147
Ah, okay.

45:26.024 --> 45:27.425
Feed me, what do we got?

45:27.558 --> 45:28.827
<i>You remember
to take your fish oil?</i>

45:28.960 --> 45:29.761
I did. <i>- B-12?</i>

45:29.895 --> 45:31.362
Did it. <i>- L-arginine?</i>

45:31.496 --> 45:33.231
Got 'em all. Next.

45:33.364 --> 45:35.533
<i>You're supposed to file
that appellate brief
for Hemple by 4:00.</i>

45:35.666 --> 45:37.836
Crap. Um, hey,

45:37.969 --> 45:40.839
could you put down
the travel magazine
and help with that?

45:40.972 --> 45:42.040
<i>Not a paralegal, Saul.</i>

45:43.241 --> 45:45.310
<i>Anyway, your 12:30
just walked in.</i>

45:45.443 --> 45:46.644
Aces. Send him in.

45:48.046 --> 45:49.948
Oh! Enter, Sunshine.

45:50.081 --> 45:52.583
Cast some light
into my cold, dark world.

46:09.267 --> 46:10.936
Hello?
You're on the clock, right?

46:11.069 --> 46:13.304
So give with the info anytime.

46:13.438 --> 46:14.940
When you're done.

46:15.073 --> 46:16.307
No, I can multitask, please.

46:18.076 --> 46:20.178
I'm not gonna talk to you
while you're on...

46:20.311 --> 46:23.014
whatever that is.

46:23.148 --> 46:25.984
You know, LBJ used to have
his underlings give him reports

46:26.117 --> 46:27.618
while he was on the shitter.

46:28.719 --> 46:30.088
Uh-huh.

46:30.221 --> 46:33.624
Well, either I'm gonna leave,

46:33.758 --> 46:36.261
or I'm gonna put my foot
in your skull.

46:38.296 --> 46:39.430
Fine.

46:43.101 --> 46:44.602
But you should try
one of these.

46:45.736 --> 46:47.805
You walk like Frankenstein

46:47.939 --> 46:49.975
after he was probed by aliens.

46:50.108 --> 46:52.310
I can get you one.

46:52.443 --> 46:55.346
It would do wonders
for your chi.

46:59.084 --> 47:00.785
Let's go, lay it on me.

47:05.924 --> 47:07.292
All right. First.

47:08.759 --> 47:10.996
There's your
Mrs. Denise Gabler.

47:11.129 --> 47:12.297
She's cheating, all right.

47:14.132 --> 47:16.101
Limber.

47:16.234 --> 47:17.903
Ha-ha!

47:18.036 --> 47:20.171
Well, at least I know
they didn't spot you.

47:20.305 --> 47:21.572
No one could stay that aroused

47:21.706 --> 47:23.308
with your mug
peeking through the window.

47:26.111 --> 47:27.712
What else you got?

47:27.845 --> 47:30.048
Well, next,
I followed your bus driver.

47:30.181 --> 47:32.717
News flash. He really
does have a broken neck.

47:32.850 --> 47:35.220
Fantastic.

47:35.353 --> 47:37.388
That makes my life much easier.

47:37.522 --> 47:38.689
Keep it coming.

47:38.823 --> 47:40.491
Second story guy
out of Indianapolis.

47:40.625 --> 47:43.361
Lasky. Did a dime at Menard.

47:43.494 --> 47:44.829
Now, if you're looking
for a talent

47:44.963 --> 47:46.864
who'll keep his mouth shut,
you can trust him.

47:46.998 --> 47:49.167
I say he's worth
keeping an eye on.

47:49.300 --> 47:51.069
Second story guy,
second story guy.

47:51.202 --> 47:53.538
I got-- I got more
second story guys in my book

47:53.671 --> 47:55.706
than pimples
at a Junior prom.

47:58.309 --> 48:01.346
What about, uh,
that Heisenberg fella?

48:03.381 --> 48:05.150
High school chemistry teacher.

48:06.051 --> 48:08.086
You're shittin' me. Really?

48:08.219 --> 48:10.155
Walter Hartwell White.

48:10.288 --> 48:13.058
Chemistry teacher
over at JP Wynne.

48:13.191 --> 48:15.660
Working with a former student,
current meth head,

48:15.793 --> 48:16.861
one Jesse Pinkman.

48:16.995 --> 48:17.862
Wow.

48:19.064 --> 48:21.099
Uh, what else
about the teacher?

48:21.232 --> 48:23.234
He has lung cancer.

48:24.202 --> 48:25.270
Jesus.

48:27.205 --> 48:28.974
That's why he can't quit
with the coughing.

48:30.041 --> 48:31.076
How bad?

48:31.209 --> 48:32.910
Stage Three A.

48:33.044 --> 48:34.912
He's in treatment,
more tests to come,

48:35.046 --> 48:36.581
but it doesn't look good.

48:36.714 --> 48:38.449
Now, listen, even if
this guy was gonna live,

48:38.583 --> 48:39.917
I wouldn't go near him.

48:40.051 --> 48:41.386
He's a complete amateur.

48:41.519 --> 48:43.554
Well, you see an amateur.

48:43.688 --> 48:47.592
I see...
170 pounds of clay
ready to be molded.

48:47.725 --> 48:49.527
Well, if the cancer
doesn't get him,

48:49.660 --> 48:51.796
it'll be the cops
or a bullet to the head.

48:53.698 --> 48:55.967
Is that your appraisal
or is that what

48:56.101 --> 48:58.569
"He-Who-Shall-Not-Be-Named"
says about him?

48:58.703 --> 49:01.672
He doesn't say anything.
The guy's small potatoes.

49:01.806 --> 49:03.308
Yeah, okay. I hear you.

49:03.441 --> 49:04.809
I just--

49:04.942 --> 49:06.777
I got a feeling about this.

49:06.911 --> 49:09.447
This Heisenberg guy's
got something.

49:09.580 --> 49:12.317
It's top of the line product,
that's the buzz on the street,

49:12.450 --> 49:13.584
and I just think,
with the right management--

49:13.718 --> 49:15.987
You know, years ago,
I bought a Betamax.

49:16.121 --> 49:17.588
Good product.
"Top of the line."

49:17.722 --> 49:21.059
Experts said
it was better than a VHS.

49:21.192 --> 49:24.195
Turned out to be a complete
waste of time and money.

49:24.329 --> 49:25.263
Hmm?

49:25.963 --> 49:26.797
Let it go.

49:29.434 --> 49:31.469
Guy with that mustache

49:31.602 --> 49:33.538
probably doesn't make
a lot of good life choices.

49:33.671 --> 49:36.641
So, yeah, uh,
the second story guy.

49:36.774 --> 49:39.110
- Uh, Menard, you said?
- Yeah, right, right, right.

49:40.745 --> 49:42.580
All right,
part of a high-end crew

49:42.713 --> 49:44.815
fencing jewelry up into Canada.

49:46.551 --> 49:48.653
Now, the Lasky kid
caught a bad break.

49:48.786 --> 49:51.322
The cop was driving by
just as he was ducking
in a window.

49:52.557 --> 49:54.292
He did the time,

49:54.425 --> 49:58.496
no one else on his crew
went down. Solid.

49:58.629 --> 50:01.132
<i>Known for their vast migration
patterns through Africa,</i>

50:01.266 --> 50:02.833
<i>nearly two million wildebeests</i>

50:02.967 --> 50:04.802
<i>travel 2,000 miles each year...</i>

50:06.537 --> 50:09.140
<i>...making their migration
one of the greatest on Earth.</i>

50:13.211 --> 50:15.713
<i>The herd seeks fresh grass,
following the rain
through Kenya and Tanzania.</i>

50:15.846 --> 50:19.450
<i>Gathering each year
to prepare for the journey,</i>

50:19.584 --> 50:22.853
<i>one that's been taking place
for a million years.</i>

50:24.755 --> 50:26.324
<i>The voyage is not easy.</i>

50:26.457 --> 50:31.096
<i>While traveling, the herd
must stay well fed, rested</i>

50:31.229 --> 50:34.765
<i>and free of disease
or be left behi--</i>

50:34.899 --> 50:37.535
<i>Couple more.
And shuffle, ladies.</i>

50:39.237 --> 50:40.371
<i>Just like that.</i>

50:42.373 --> 50:43.708
[headset beeping, vibrating] <i>- Now L step.</i>

50:46.010 --> 50:47.145
<i>Four times.</i>

50:49.046 --> 50:50.815
<i>Fabulous!</i>

50:50.948 --> 50:52.883
<i>Let me see you having fun.</i>

50:53.017 --> 50:54.051
Yeah.

50:56.721 --> 50:58.089
W-- Uh.

50:58.223 --> 50:58.923
What do you mean?

51:02.160 --> 51:03.094
He what?

51:05.830 --> 51:09.700
Tell-- Tell him to get his ass
back to the garage right now.

51:14.205 --> 51:15.706
You cutie-patootie.

51:19.210 --> 51:21.412
You think you've seen everything.

51:44.235 --> 51:46.971
Shut that goddamn dog up
and get back in here.

51:50.841 --> 51:51.576
Get in.

51:56.247 --> 51:59.116
You're kidding me.
You're absolutely kidding me.

51:59.250 --> 52:00.318
I'm sorry, man. I couldn't--

52:00.451 --> 52:02.287
Do you know how much time,
how much effort,

52:02.420 --> 52:04.289
I put into finding
the perfect mark?

52:04.422 --> 52:06.090
I have to weed through
all these saps

52:06.224 --> 52:08.693
who have wives
and families at home,

52:08.826 --> 52:10.761
find somebody
who's alone with money,

52:10.895 --> 52:13.498
and, what,
so you can just wimp out?

52:13.631 --> 52:14.999
The guy has cancer, man.

52:15.132 --> 52:17.302
I found pills in his pocket.

52:17.435 --> 52:19.170
Okay? The same ones
my dad took.

52:19.304 --> 52:20.405
For, like, pancreatic cancer.

52:20.538 --> 52:22.740
So? A guy with cancer
can't be an asshole?

52:22.873 --> 52:25.776
Believe me,
I speak from experience.

52:25.910 --> 52:28.246
I can't rip off a guy
with cancer. I'm sorry.

52:28.379 --> 52:31.182
Do you know how many
of the suckers we've ripped off
have sob stories?

52:31.316 --> 52:32.617
Every single one of them.

52:33.651 --> 52:35.119
Besides, it'll be months

52:35.253 --> 52:36.821
before they even realize
they've been taken.

52:36.954 --> 52:38.389
This guy will already be dead.

52:38.523 --> 52:39.724
So, please,
get back in your truck,

52:39.857 --> 52:41.492
go back to the house,
and finish the job.

52:46.063 --> 52:48.633
No, man. I can't do that.

52:48.766 --> 52:49.900
I can't.

52:50.034 --> 52:51.636
Look, all right.
I get it.

52:52.470 --> 52:54.171
You get over it, okay?

52:54.305 --> 52:55.773
Please, believe me. Y--

52:55.906 --> 52:58.509
Before you know it,
you forget all about it.

52:58.643 --> 52:59.510
Go.

53:01.879 --> 53:03.881
Well, l-look,
we're doing really well, right?

53:04.014 --> 53:05.650
Hear me out, okay?
I mean, we're rolling in cash.

53:06.684 --> 53:08.052
We can just let this one go.

53:08.185 --> 53:09.454
Not your call.

53:09.587 --> 53:13.090
Yeah, but I,
I pulled the tape when I left.

53:13.224 --> 53:14.392
The door's locked.

53:14.525 --> 53:15.760
We couldn't get back in
even if we wanted to.

53:18.596 --> 53:20.965
Jeff, come on, man,
back me up here.

53:21.999 --> 53:23.401
Huh?

53:23.534 --> 53:24.835
Oh, well... I, I don't know.

53:24.969 --> 53:27.838
I mean, I can see
both sides, kinda.

53:27.972 --> 53:29.474
You know, forget it.
You're fired. Just go.

53:29.607 --> 53:30.675
Just gimme the camera and go.

53:32.176 --> 53:33.511
Fine.

53:33.644 --> 53:36.180
Good. Go. We don't need you.

53:36.314 --> 53:37.948
And I know
I don't need to tell you this,

53:38.082 --> 53:39.584
but since you're
such a goddamned amateur,

53:39.717 --> 53:41.419
I will anyway.

53:41.552 --> 53:42.753
Keep your mouth shut.

53:56.534 --> 53:58.202
If we're gonna do this,
we should leave now.

53:59.904 --> 54:01.205
We're really
gonna go back there?

54:02.473 --> 54:03.308
What'd I just say?

54:05.109 --> 54:05.910
Jeff, are you in or out?

54:23.328 --> 54:24.094
What?

54:25.430 --> 54:27.031
I'm down for this. I am.

54:27.164 --> 54:29.734
- But, uh...
- But what?

54:29.867 --> 54:31.302
What time did the guy
take the drugs?

54:31.436 --> 54:33.438
We gave it to him, what?
Three hours ago?

54:33.571 --> 54:35.105
I don't even know
if he finished it.

54:35.239 --> 54:36.273
He might be awake by now.

54:36.407 --> 54:37.908
Don't worry about it.

54:38.042 --> 54:39.344
Yeah, but--

54:39.477 --> 54:40.945
I said don't worry about it.

54:41.078 --> 54:41.812
It'll be fine.

54:55.626 --> 54:56.961
That's it. Right there.

55:04.101 --> 55:06.971
Come back
and get me in 20 minutes.

55:07.104 --> 55:09.173
Just roll up slow,
like you're picking up a fare.

55:10.441 --> 55:12.777
It'll be fine. Relax.
